<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-11-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-11-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="689" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d689">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Springer</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-11-19"><hi rend="italic">November 19,
                                    1896</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 165.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose for your information and such
                            action as the exigency of the case demands, a copy of a letter from Mrs.
                            Emmie Laborde, transmitting a communication from Alfred Laborde, master
                            of the <hi rend="italic">Competitor</hi>, relative to a new trial of the
                            men of the <hi rend="italic">Competitor</hi>.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. W. Rockhill.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>